--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INFORMATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Name   : socat
Type   : Ansible role

Authors: liv community
License: Simplified BSD License

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Socat is a relay for bidirectional data transfer between two independent data
channels. Each of these data channels may be a file, pipe, device (serial line
etc. or a pseudo terminal), a socket (UNIX, IP4, IP6 - raw, UDP, TCP), an SSL
socket, proxy CONNECT connection, a file descriptor (stdin etc.), the GNU line
editor (readline), a program, or a combination of two of these.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: socat
    vars:
      socat_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: socat
    vars:
      socat_state: 'remove'

INACTIVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: socat
    vars:
      socat_state: 'inactive'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PARAMETERS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  socat_state
    Description: Control the state of the role.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Predetermined
    Type       : String
    Default    : 'install'
    Options    :
      Install : 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
      Remove  : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
      Inactive: 'quiesce' | 'inactive'

